reviewText: The exercise portion of the video itself, so far, is not bad. It seems like the video is more to see who can be the most energetic and bubbly while not cuing what your are supposed to do. It's like they're auditioning for something. Maybe when I've done the video enough times and know what I'm doing will it better since I won't need their cues. Also there are strange camera actions going on in parts that make me feel dizzy. I think they don't understand it's an exercise video for us not a place to perform for them. I'm going middle of the road in my rating although I'm not sure if I will actually do this video much since it's annoying.
Great video for getting the heart rate up.  Good exercise routine.  Reasonable price.

I was disappointed with this purchase because  I already have this one on VHS. The cover was misleading because she was wearing pink DVD cover as opposed to blue spandex she wore in VHS cover. I like her fitness videos, but its misleading for consumers, there isn't much info on content and cover not always same picture.
Great exercise video. You will get two good 20 minute workout videos on this tape. Low-impact and high-impact exercises are offered. You will work up a sweat and loose weight.

I do a lot of aerobics and work out videos and right now I'm not loving this one.  The moves are switched around too quickly and with that, not a lot of direction on what will happen next.  Now maybe I need to do it a few more times to memorize the steps to enjoy it more....? I also find the people in this video a little irritating.

Tried and true. Been using this one for 20 years. Have tried others, but none are as good. Easy to follow and enough variety to keep engaged. Happy this continues to be preserved. This is my 3rd one, after wearing out each of the first two.
This replaces a VHS version.  I've always enjoyed these two workouts and I'm glad to have access to them again.
